Title : Jane Cumberbatch
Text : '''Jane Cumberbatch''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[interior design]]er and [[author]], based in [[London]].<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/property/house-and-home/a-home-office-thats-smart-and-casual-how-to-make-a-house-into-a-great-workspace-6285543.html "A home office that's smart and casual: How to make a house into a great workspace"]. Huma Qureshi.  ''The Independent'', 5 January 2012</ref><ref>[http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/style/article132900.ece "Jane Cumberbatch"]. ''Sunday Times'',  May 15, 2005, Alice Douglas</ref>  She is the originator of the decorating philosophy "Pure Style," which emphasizes simplicity, thrift, and longevity.<ref>[http://www.independent.ie/life/home-garden/interiors/a-squeeze-of-lemon-give-your-home-a-hint-of-spring-34725883.html "A squeeze of Lemon - give your home a hint of spring"]. ''The Independent''. 27 July 2016. Ciara Elliot</ref> Her designs emphasize a simplified [[aesthetic]] which includes white walls, muted colors, natural textures, and vintage elements.<ref name=Guardian>Abrahams, C. (2008, December 14). [https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2008/dec/14/jane-cumberbatch-interior-design-homes-style "Beyond the Pale: Inside Jane Cumberbatch's all-white house".] ''The Guardian''. Retrieved July 12, 2014, from</ref> She is the author of seven books, including ''Pure Style''<ref>{{cite book|title=Country Living|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZPvxAAAAMAAJ|year=1996|publisher=Hearst Corporation|page=288}}</ref> and the [[cookbook]] ''Recipes for Every Day''.<ref>[http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-1-86205-912-2 "Jane Cumberbatchâ€™s Recipes for Every Day"]. ''Publishers Weekly''</ref>

==Career==
Cumberbatch worked as decorating editor for the [[magazine]] ''British House and Garden'',<ref>Finlay, L. (n.d.). Inside design: Jane Cumberbatch.  Retrieved July 12, 2014, from http://www.styleathome.com/decorating-and-design/inside-design/inside-design-jane-cumberbatch/a/814</ref><ref>[http://www.dailyimprint.net/2009/02/designinspiration-jane-cumberbatch.html "designer jane cumberbatch"]. ''Daily Imprint'', 12 February 2009.</ref> as well as for Elle Decoration,<ref>Soissons, S. d. (2011, July 14). [http://thefoodiebugle.com/article/cookbooks/pure-style.-recipes-for-every-day-by-jane-cumberbatch "Pure Style. Recipes for Every Day by Jane Cumberbatch"]. ''The Foodie Bugle'', Retrieved July 12, 2014, from</ref> and the [[The_Sunday_Telegraph|Sunday Telegraph Magazine]].<ref>[http://www.quadrille.com/author/jane-cumberbatch/35 "Jane Cumberbatch"]. ''Quadrille''. (n.d.). Retrieved July 12, 2014, from</ref> Cumberbatch's London house has been featured on the BBC Series ''Lead Balloon''.<ref name=Guardian />

In 2015 she wrote the book ''Pure Style'', published by Pavilion.<ref>[http://thechromologist.com/summer-reading-list-pure-colour-jane-cumberbatch/ "Summer Reading List: Pure Colour by Jane Cumberbatch"]. ''The Chromologist'', Jill Macnair 4 June 2015</ref><ref>[http://luxuryreading.com/purestyle/ "Review: Pure Style: Recipes for Every Day by Jane Cumberbatch"]. ''Luxury Reading'', Reviewed by Alisha Churbe</ref>  In 2016 she published a companion book, ''Pure Colour''.<ref>[http://www.architecturaldigest.com/gallery/vibrant-color-combinations-room-refresh "6 Vibrant Color Combinations for a Room Refresh"]. ''Architectural Digest'', Lindsey Mather. Posted May 25, 2016</ref>

